http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/PM-determined-to-assist-Seema-says-Gowda/article13990186.ece

Prime Minister Narendra Modi is striving hard to place India on the global arena in terms of development and was going ahead with good governance, Union Minister for Law and Justice D.V. Sadananda Gowda said on Friday.Addressing judicial officers and advocates at the district courts complex here, Mr. Gowda said he would apprise Mr. Modi to direct States to give a boost to employment generation for youth. “The Prime Minister is determined to assist Rayalaseema, which is a backward region,” he said.The Minister said he would apprise the PM of advocates’ demand for the constitution of a National Judicial Commission. He advised judicial officers to expeditiously dispose of cases and reduce pendency of cases.